{"word":"ἀντιάζω","slug":"ἀντιάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀντιάζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀντίος'><el>ἀντίος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to meet face to face</i>,<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to encounter</i>, whether as friend or foe, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to meet, answer</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to approach as suppliants, to entreat, supplicate</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to meet in</i> fight, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}